[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police hunt three men over Perth mugging

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 27-year-old man has been mugged in Perth by three men who stole his wallet.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The victim required medical treatment at hospital for minor injuries after being approached by the men, who made off with a three-figure sum of money.
The incident happened in Ladeside, near Sports Direct, at 23:00 on Saturday.
One of the men was described as about 25-years-old, wearing a black jacket with a red collar and cuffs, with blue jeans and black shoes.
A second man was described as wearing a black jacket and blue jeans. There is no description for the third man.
Police said all three suspects spoke with Polish accents and have appealed for witnesses to contact them.
